                            <comment id="16823171" author="munendrasn" created="Mon, 22 Apr 2019 15:14:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;nobr&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/attachment/12972742/12972742_SOLR-13404.patch&quot; title=&quot;SOLR-13404.patch attached to SOLR-13404&quot;&gt;SOLR-13404.patch&lt;sup&gt;&lt;img class=&quot;rendericon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/link_attachment_7.gif&quot; height=&quot;7&quot; width=&quot;7&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;br/&gt;
This patch&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;adds support to return group.query response in distrib mode when group.main=true or group.format=simple&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Also, fixes &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-4181&quot; title=&quot;grouping response format inconsistent in distributed search when no docs match group.query&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-4181&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-4181&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Respects group.limit and group.offset when group.format=grouped and group.query is specified in distrib&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;handles negative values for group.offset. Currently, AIOOBE is thrown for -ve values&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;With this patch, group.query in distrib mode mimics the behavior of group.query in standalone mode.&lt;br/&gt;
One case not handled is when rows is -ve which is allowed in grouping. Negative value for rows in distributed grouped doesn&apos;t work properly and this issue is not limited group.query(it affects group.field too). Probably, will spinoff new issue for that&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
